==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: dyers-broom
<hw>dyer's-broom</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<def>small Eurasian shrub (<spn>Genista tinctoria</spn>) having clusters
of yellow flowers that yield a dye; common as weed in England and U.S.;
sometimes grown as an ornamental.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> woodwaxen, dyer's greenweed, dyer's weed, dyer's
rocket, dyeweed, greenweed, whin, woadwaxen, <spn>Genista
tinctoria</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dyestuff</ent>⟦br⟧
